The paper discusses a technique for software watermarking, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed method involves encoding watermarks as graph structures, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions enhancing the resilience of the codec system to attacks, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
